<br>
<br>
A note to Lances:<br>
I'm not really going to debate the merits of having deities being required to wear certain types of equipment.   It's not normally within my personal ethics to condemn one person's choices.   But I will remind you that EQ was always supposed to be a role playing game and in any immersive Fantasy world where Gods are a part of it, they SHOULD be important in some way.  <br>
<br>
Most people when creating their character chose their Deity in order to do what gamers call min/maxing the system... this means minimum expenditure for maximum results.  Because being agnostic gives the GREATEST faction benefits (ie: your faction table is generally speaking the most favorable possible after you factor your race) Verant has tried (more recently) to balance out these factors by rewarding people who are faithful to their culture and beliefs by giving deity specific benefits, recently in the form of equipment.<br>
<br>
The barbarian's follow the tribunal, so therefore if one adhered to the code, you reaped the rewards of keeping faith.<br>
<br>
Expect Verant to come up with more Deity specific quests/rewards especially with the new Planes of Power expansion coming.  I'm kind of hoping to see The Tribunal give actual quests to their followers.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, kudos to Verant, it makes for a more logical and consistent game.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/22/02 10:15:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Barbarian Smith Available</span><hr size=1> Hail,<br>
